A: You are using the same DataSnapshot object in the loop and in the add method. You should use dataSnapshot1 instead of dataSnapshot in the add method.
Here is the corrected code:
names.add(dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class));

Also, you are adding the same value multiple times because you are iterating over the children of the same DataSnapshot object in the loop. You should create a new DataSnapshot object for each child in the loop.
Here is the corrected code:
for (DataSnapshot dataSnapshot1:dataSnapshot.getChildren()) {
    i = i + 1;
    names.add(dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class));
}

And you are right, you can use an Iterator to get all the values. Here is how you can do it:
for(Iterator<DataSnapshot> it = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator(); it.hasNext(); ){
    i = i + 1;
    names.add(it.next().getValue(String.class));
}

This will give you all the values in the names list.

